   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>I. Satan s Six Great Undertakings in the Universe</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Satan has done much work in the universe.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Of these works, six are quite important and every Christian should memorize them.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>After these six great tasks, Satan s destiny will come to an end.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Rebelling</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>See Isaiah 14:13-14.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Stealing Away the First Adam</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>See Genesis 3:1-4.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Tempting the Last Adam</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>See Matthew 4:1-11.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Killing the Righteous One the Lord Jesus</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>See Acts 3:15 and 7:52.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Being Incarnated as the Antichrist</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The Bible shows us that one day Satan will also become flesh to be the Antichrist.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The coming Antichrist will be the embodiment of Satan, just as Christ is the embodiment of God.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>As Christ is the proper mingling of God and man, Antichrist will be the illegitimate mixture of Satan and man.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>See Revelation 12:9-12, 13:2, and 2 Thessalonians 2:8-9.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>6.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Deceiving at the End of the Millennium</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>See Revelation 20:7-10.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>J. Satan s Judgment 1.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Being Cast Out from the Holy Mountain of God</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Satan was originally God s anointed cherub, who stood before God upon the holy mountain where God dwelt.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>When he rebelled against God because of his pride, he was cast out by God from the holy mountain.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>This is recorded in Ezekiel 28:16-17.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Being Judged and Destroyed</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>by the Lord on the Cross</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>On the cross, the Lord not only bore man s sins, He also destroyed Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Through death, the Lord Jesus destroyed the devil, who has the might of death.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>See Hebrews 2:14, John 12:31, and 16:11.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Being Cast Down to the Earth</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>As soon as the overcomers are caught up to heaven, Satan will be cast down from heaven to the earth.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>See Revelation 12:8-10 and 13.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Being Bound and Cast into the Abyss</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>for One Thousand Years</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>See Revelation 20:1-3 and compare with Isaiah 14:15.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>Being Cast into the Lake of Fire</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>See Revelation 20:10.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>The ultimate end of Satan will be to be cast into the lake of fire.</S>
   </TEXT>
